parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crank bearing can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: The engine makes a loud knocking sound
and the vehicle may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lag and hesitation in the DCT transmission can cause the vehicle to slow down or lose power, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when merging into traffic or turning into oncoming traffic.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or lags when accelerating from low speeds
especially when turning or merging into traffic; the vehicle may not respond to throttle input for 1-3 seconds; and sudden jerking or lurching forward when the transmission finally engages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rod bearings can cause the engine to seize, resulting in loss of power and control, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: and inability to restart the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle actuator problem can cause the engine to go into limp mode, resulting in loss of power and acceleration, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including loss of vehicle functionality, failure to start, and increased risk of accidents or fires.
The failure of the coil pack can cause engine misfires, smoke, and fires, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the headlight insulation can cause a fire hazard, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the passenger restraint system can cause a failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Passenger restraint fault light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SOS system can cause a failure of emergency services to respond in the event of an accident, which can lead to delayed medical attention and increased risk of injuries or fatalities.
